      • getFirst

        public T getFirst()
        The getFirst() method will return the first element in the linked list. This is done by simply by pulling the 'data' of Node front.
        Returns:
        the first element in the linked list

      • getNext

        public T getNext()
        The getNext() method will return the next method in the linked list. This is done by creating a clone of the front of the list and using a 'for loop' through a simple algorithm designed to yield the next element, as many times as the method counter suggests. We do this since the position of the nodes can change.
        Returns:
        the next element in the linked list.
